The paper discusses the use of human-robot interaction in training reinforcement learning algorithms, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and robotics (cs.RO). The paper also discusses the different types of human interaction, such as demonstration and evaluation, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The paper also presents a framework for autonomous systems, which involves machine learning (cs.LG) and control systems (cs.SY).
